(58, 1, 'Private Limited Company Incorporation', 'private-limited-company-incorporation', '<p>Private limited companies are considered to be the best choice for a start-up. They are separate legal entities under the law and find it easy to raise funds to run their business.</p>', '<p><strong>What is a Private Limited Company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Private limited companies are considered to be the best choice for a start-up. They are separate legal entities under the law and find it easy to raise funds to run their business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of a private limited company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The shareholders of the company hold a limited liability in the company</li>\r\n	<li>The private companies have separate legal entities unlike the partnership firms</li>\r\n	<li>The company can borrow money for running the business through the financial institutions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register as a private limited company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The company is a separate legal entity and has no personal liability to the creditors</li>\r\n	<li>The company can have its roots both in India and abroad</li>\r\n	<li>The company gets a unique name</li>\r\n	<li>Business ownership can be transferred from one person to another by transferring the shares</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Legal existence</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike the public and the partnership firms, the private limited company is considered as a separate legal entity under the laws. This in turn helps in reducing the legal liability of the directors and the shareholders in the private limited company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Value for business</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Private limited companies have better credibility among the people, as information about their firm can easily be accessed on the public databases. With people recognizing the companies easily, their business value increases within a short time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Access to funding</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Private limited companies have the advantage of expanding their hold on the business to certain international ventures. This way, you are able to get hold of the international funding for your businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PAN card of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>ID and Address proof of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>The signed DSC form</li>\r\n	<li>Passport Size Photograph of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>Proof of ownership or rental agreement between the directors and the landlord</li>\r\n	<li>Latest utility bill statement for the registered office space</li>\r\n	<li>NOC from the landlord with legal notarization</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Digital Signature Certificate and the Director Identification Number for the proposed directors for the company must be obtained.</li>\r\n	<li>Get an approval for the name chosen for the company.</li>\r\n	<li>Register the required documents and get them verified.</li>\r\n	<li>Company can be registered once the verification is complete.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:37:\"Private Limited Company Incorporation\";s:11:\"description\";s:180:\"Private limited companies are considered to be the best choice for a start-up. They are separate legal entities under the law and find it easy to raise funds to run their business.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544351698_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:01:01', '2018-12-10 18:16:13'),
(59, 1, 'LLP Registration', 'llp-registration', '<p>Limited Liability Partnership is a result of a combination between the private limited company and the partnership system. As such, LLP is a partnership that comes with ceratin limited liabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>What is a limited liability partnership?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Limited Liability Partnership is a result of a combination between the private limited company and the partnership system. As such, LLP is a partnership that comes with ceratin limited liabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of limited liability partnership?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Limited Liability Partnership is considered as separate legal entities from their members.</li>\r\n	<li>The members have the facility of limited liability.</li>\r\n	<li>The LLP is taxed together as a partnership.</li>\r\n	<li>They have the ability to create floating charges.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register for a LLP?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In a LLP, one partner is not liable for the action of the other partner</li>\r\n	<li>Audit for the business is not required for a low turnover amount</li>\r\n	<li>Property can be owned by the LLP, though the ownership cannot be claimed by individual partners</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Careful drafting</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A LLP agreement is considered to be one of the most important documents for a business. Therefore, it is required on the part of the directors or the shareholders to make sure that every clause in the document is drafted carefully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yearly compliance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As such, LLP has a easy compliance as they are considered to be separate legal entities under the law. In this case, the yearly compliance that needs to be done for the business can be done without any complication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unique identity</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you register your LLP, the company will get a unique name. The business carried out by this company will be done under the name that has been provided during the time of registration.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PAN card of the shareholders and directors</li>\r\n	<li>ID proof of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>Passport size photograph of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>The signed DSC form</li>\r\n	<li>Latest utility bill statement for the place chosen for operating the business</li>\r\n	<li>Rental agreement or ownership proof for the space</li>\r\n	<li>NOC from the landlord of the office space</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Digital Signature Certificate and the Designated Partner Identification Number must be obtained</li>\r\n	<li>Approval for the name of the company must be obtained</li>\r\n	<li>The documents must be submitted for verification and the LLP agreement must be signed</li>\r\n	<li>The LLP can be incorporated after document verification</li>\r\n</ul>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"LLP Registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:197:\"Limited Liability Partnership is a result of a combination between the private limited company and the partnership system. As such, LLP is a partnership that comes with ceratin limited liabilities.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544351821_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:07:01', '2018-12-10 18:16:04'),
(60, 1, 'One person company registration', 'one-person-company-registration', '<p>Considered to be the perfect opportunity for the start-ups and the entrepreneurs, One Person Company has only a single owner or shareholder. This is a type of private limited company.</p>', '<p><strong>What is a one person company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Considered to be the perfect opportunity for the start-ups and the entrepreneurs, One Person Company has only a single owner or shareholder. This is a type of private limited company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of a one person company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The one person company is a private company</li>\r\n	<li>The term one person company is mentioned under the name of the company</li>\r\n	<li>Limited liability protection is provided to the sole shareholder</li>\r\n	<li>Single director is enough to sign the financial and the director&rsquo;s report</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register as a one person company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>As the firm is owned by a single person, the ownership can be transferred from one person to another if there is a need</li>\r\n	<li>The perpetual existence of the business is ensured in all cases</li>\r\n	<li>A single person is enough to start and run the OPC</li>\r\n	<li>Limited legal liability is provided to the single person owning the OPC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reputation for the business</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you register the company in India, you are able to get an International level recognition for the company. This helps in increasing the business value for the company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Separate legal entity</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>OPC is considered as a separate legal entity under the law. In such cases, the promoter of the business is able to get the help for funding their business in the form of loans from banking institutions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unique company name</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you register the name of the company, you are required to add the OPC under the approved name to help the people that you are running the company as a single person and there are no more directors except you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PAN card of the person starting the OPC</li>\r\n	<li>ID and Address proof of the promoter of the OPC</li>\r\n	<li>Passport size photograph of the person starting the OPC</li>\r\n	<li>The signed DSC form</li>\r\n	<li>Rental agreement for the place chosen for starting the business</li>\r\n	<li>The latest utility bills for the chosen place</li>\r\n	<li>NOC from the landlord owning the place</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Digital Signature Certificate and the Director Identification Number of the single promoter of OPC must be obtained</li>\r\n	<li>Get the approval for the name of your OPC</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the documents and file for the incorporation of the OPC</li>\r\n</ul>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:31:\"One person company registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:183:\"Considered to be the perfect opportunity for the start-ups and the entrepreneurs, One Person Company has only a single owner or shareholder. This is a type of private limited company.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544352031_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePage', 42, '2018-12-08 20:10:31', '2018-12-08 20:10:31'),
(61, 1, 'Partnership registration', 'partnership-registration', '<p>Under the partnership firm, two or more individuals come together in agreement to become partners to run a business. They are easy to start and most of the partnership firms in existence today are either small or medium firms.</p>', '<p><strong>What is a partnership firm?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Under the partnership firm, two or more individuals come together in agreement to become partners to run a business. They are easy to start and most of the partnership firms in existence today are either small or medium firms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of a partnership firm?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The legal document mentioning the partnership between two entities is enough for creating the partnership.</li>\r\n	<li>The profits obtained out of the business are shared equally among all the partners.</li>\r\n	<li>The nature of liability maintained by the partners is similar to that of the sole proprietorship.</li>\r\n	<li>The control over the management rests with each of the partners.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register as a partnership firm?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Unlike the other companies, the partnership form does not have to file for the annual accounts with the registrar</li>\r\n	<li>The partnership firm can have any name of their choice after agreement between the partners in the firm</li>\r\n	<li>Without much of the legal compliances bring you down, the partnership firms are easy to start</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Number of partners</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The minimum number of partners for starting the partnership firm is two, while there can be even more members as partners for a particular business. All profits and losses are shared equally by the partners.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Partnership firm registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Registration of the partnership firms is a must if you wish to bring case in the business to the court. Also, if you do not want any usage of the business name for other activities, registration is a must.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Relationship with the firm</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The partners are not considered to be a separate entity from the firm. As the partners are involved in the business together, they are liable for the events taking place in the name of the partnership firm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Form No. 1</li>\r\n	<li>Original copy of the partnership deed bearing the signature of all the partners</li>\r\n	<li>Declaration affidavit showing the proof of partnership intent between the partners</li>\r\n	<li>Rental agreement of the place chosen to run the business for the partnership firm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Draft a deed to show proof for the partnership between two more entities</li>\r\n	<li>Register the partnership deed with the required authorities</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain the PAN and the TAN for the registered partnership firm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:24:\"Partnership registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:226:\"Under the partnership firm, two or more individuals come together in agreement to become partners to run a business. They are easy to start and most of the partnership firms in existence today are either small or medium firms.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544352168_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:12:48', '2018-12-10 18:16:31'),
(62, 1, 'Proprietorship Registration', 'proprietorship-registration', '<p>Majorly used by the small and the medium sized businesses, proprietorship forms are started and managed by a single person. They are easy to start and do not have much regulatory compliances.</p>', '<p><strong>What is a proprietorship firm?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Majorly used by the small and the medium sized businesses, proprietorship forms are started and managed by a single person. They are easy to start and do not have much regulatory compliances.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of the proprietorship firm?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A single individual runs the entire the company.</li>\r\n	<li>The individual gains the complete control over all the proceedings of the company.</li>\r\n	<li>The person is liable for all the debts incurred by the company.</li>\r\n	<li>The sole proprietorship does not have much complex filing systems.</li>\r\n	<li>Sole proprietorships are easy to start up.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register as a proprietorship firm?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Proprietorship firms that make less turnover have the facility of paying lesser tax returns</li>\r\n	<li>Even if you wish to close the proprietorship, you will find it easy to close, as both the firm and the proprietor are considered same under law</li>\r\n	<li>The proprietorship is registered and managed by a single person</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ease of start</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The time taken to start a proprietorship is less when compared to the other companies. If you have the authentic PAN card and the address proof with you, you can easily apply for a proprietorship under your name.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Inexpensive</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As mentioned, since there are very minimal regulatory compliances, you do not have to worry about the expenses that you have to incur while forming a proprietorship firm. No external help is required for starting the business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Compliances</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Proprietorship firms are regulated by the government under which they are regulated. As the jurisdiction for the firm is not diverse, you can see that the person does not have to go through a lot of complex compliances to start the business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PAN card of the sole proprietor</li>\r\n	<li>Address and identity proof for the sole proprietor</li>\r\n	<li>KYC documents</li>\r\n	<li>Rental agreement between the proprietor and the landlord for the place of operation of the proprietorship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get consultation for starting of the proprietorship</li>\r\n	<li>Apply for the tax registration under the proprietorship name</li>\r\n	<li>File the documents for the registration of the proprietorship with the authorities</li>\r\n	<li>Open a bank account to handle the finances of the proprietorship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:27:\"Proprietorship Registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:191:\"Majorly used by the small and the medium sized businesses, proprietorship forms are started and managed by a single person. They are easy to start and do not have much regulatory compliances.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544352311_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePage', 42, '2018-12-08 20:15:11', '2018-12-08 20:15:11'),
(63, 1, 'Public limited company incorporation', 'public-limited-company-incorporation', '<p>Public limited company mostly deals with the large corporate houses including the factories and the industries. Unlike the private firms, they have certain compliances that must be adhered to for the proper functioning of the company.</p>', '<p><strong>What is a public limited company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Public limited company mostly deals with the large corporate houses including the factories and the industries. Unlike the private firms, they have certain compliances that must be adhered to for the proper functioning of the company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of Public limited company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The shareholders hold liability over the share they have contributed for the company.</li>\r\n	<li>The shares in the company can be bought and sold over the stock exchange.</li>\r\n	<li>The shares of the deceased shareholder would be transferred to the next of kin.</li>\r\n	<li>The financial documents of the company are carefully regulated and must be produced before the law as and when required.</li>\r\n	<li>The companies have the facility of raising the capital when required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register as a public limited company?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Public limited company follow a structured succession of ownership in their business, thereby ensuring continued existence of the firm</li>\r\n	<li>The company gets better funding options and have the liberty of gaining financial assistance whenever they want</li>\r\n	<li>The company can have a property of its own under the company&rsquo;s name</li>\r\n	<li>They are considered as separate legal entities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you need to know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Funding options</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Banking institutions and other funding organizations are glad to provide the funding for the public limited company. The companies are able to get the best funding options for running their business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Starting the company</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unlike the other companies, starting a public limited company is a bit of a costly affair, as there are factors to be considered. This is one of the reasons why the large corporate bodies take up this, rather than the small businesses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Members in the company</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is no limit to the maximum number of members in the company during their incorporation, though a minimum of seven members are required during registration of the company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PAN card of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>ID and Address proof of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>Passport size photograph of the directors and the shareholders</li>\r\n	<li>Signed DSC form</li>\r\n	<li>Rental agreement document or the proof of ownership of the place chosen to run the business</li>\r\n	<li>The latest utility bills for the place</li>\r\n	<li>NOC from the landlord</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Digital Signature Certificate and Director Identification Number must be filed</li>\r\n	<li>Approval for the name of the company must be obtained</li>\r\n	<li>Required documents must be submitted and will be verified</li>\r\n	<li>The company can be incorporated after verification of the documents</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:36:\"Public limited company incorporation\";s:11:\"description\";s:234:\"Public limited company mostly deals with the large corporate houses including the factories and the industries. Unlike the private firms, they have certain compliances that must be adhered to for the proper functioning of the company.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544352567_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:19:27', '2018-12-10 18:18:02'),
(64, 1, 'Food license registration', 'food-license-registration', '<p>Food license is issued to the people who are involved in the food packing, storing, manufacturing and the export business. It is required for every person to get this license to take up the work in the food industry.</p>', '<p><strong>What is the food license?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Food license is issued to the people who are involved in the food packing, storing, manufacturing and the export business. It is required for every person to get this license to take up the work in the food industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of food license?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The Food license is issued by the FSSAI</li>\r\n	<li>All food manufacturing and distributing units must register under the FSAAI before commencing their activity</li>\r\n	<li>The license is provided to the units only if they comply with the norms set by the FSSAI</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register for the food license?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Food license helps to understand the quality of the food manufactured and distributed by the particular unit</li>\r\n	<li>All food manufacturing units and the hotels and restaurants need the food license</li>\r\n	<li>The license can be renewed once the term ends</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Validity</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The food license is valid for up to two years after the person registers with the FSSAI. The same can be renewed to continue with the food manufacturing and distribution activity in the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Food licenses</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>State level and central licenses are issued under the food licenses. The hotels and restaurants come under the state level licenses, while the large food manufacturers must take up the central license.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Exemptions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The cottage industry and the small scale stallholders are exempt from the food license registration. This also includes the hawkers and the tiny food business operator.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Layout of the processing unit</li>\r\n	<li>List of directors and partners</li>\r\n	<li>ID and address proof of the directors and partners</li>\r\n	<li>Rental agreement or sales deed for the place of operation</li>\r\n	<li>List of food categories to be manufactured</li>\r\n	<li>Analysis report of the place</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Fill and submit the Form B on the official website</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the documents for verification</li>\r\n	<li>Register for the food license</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:25:\"Food license registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:216:\"Food license is issued to the people who are involved in the food packing, storing, manufacturing and the export business. It is required for every person to get this license to take up the work in the food industry.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544352871_img1.jpg', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:24:31', '2018-12-10 18:18:20'),
(65, 1, 'GST Registration in India', 'gst-registration-in-india', '<p>This is one of the recent tax forms introduced in India and encompasses other forms of taxes levied as VAT, service tax, entertainment and luxury tax, and excise duty. It is mandatory for the person to register for the GST tax if their turnover is more than 20 lakhs and if they are a inter-state or e-commerce trader.</p>', '<p><strong>What is Goods and Service tax?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is one of the recent tax forms introduced in India and encompasses other forms of taxes levied as VAT, service tax, entertainment and luxury tax, and excise duty. It is mandatory for the person to register for the GST tax if their turnover is more than 20 lakhs and if they are a inter-state or e-commerce trader.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of Goods and Service Tax?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The GST tax registration is mandatory for every person within the interstate</li>\r\n	<li>The GST tax has an access to single tax across all the states in India</li>\r\n	<li>This is mandatory if the person is setting up an ecommerce website in India</li>\r\n	<li>Exemption limit is available for the intrastate traders and not the interstate traders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register for GST Tax?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The person has a single access to paying the taxes in India</li>\r\n	<li>Unified access to the tax will give a better access to doing the business with ease</li>\r\n	<li>Only the people who make a higher turnover than the others are liable to pay the GST tax</li>\r\n	<li>The indirect taxes in India become streamlined and can be unified on a single platform</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know about GST Tax</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Combination of taxes</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The GST tax combines all the indirect taxes levied on the people within India. This helps in easy compliance of the taxes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Increased tax base</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unification of the taxes has seen an increase in the tax base in India. All latest technologies hare being used for management of the tax.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ease of business</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>By combining the taxes, people can now go about with the easy business norms and the intrastate traders have some basic exemptions, which is missing for the interstate traders.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Photograph of the person registering for the GST Tax</li>\r\n	<li>Constitution of the tax payer, which includes registration certificate and partnership deed</li>\r\n	<li>Proof for the place of business</li>\r\n	<li>Bank account details of the person</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submit the documents to the GST officer for verification</li>\r\n	<li>The documents are verified for its authenticity</li>\r\n	<li>GST registration certificate provided after verification</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:16:\"GST Registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:318:\"This is one of the recent tax forms introduced in India and encompasses other forms of taxes levied as VAT, service tax, entertainment and luxury tax, and excise duty. It is mandatory for the person to register for the GST tax if their turnover is more than 20 lakhs and if they are a inter-state or e-commerce trader.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544353015_img2.jpg', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:26:55', '2018-12-10 18:21:51'),
(66, 1, 'Import and Export Code registration', 'import-and-export-code-registration', '<p>It is mandatory for a person to register for the import and export code in order to carry put import and export of goods within the country legally. A 10 digit code is provided to the person who registers for the IEC.</p>', '<p><strong>What is import and export code?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is mandatory for a person to register for the import and export code in order to carry put import and export of goods within the country legally. A 10 digit code is provided to the person who registers for the IEC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of Import and Export Code?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The IEC does not apply to the technology and the services used by the people</li>\r\n	<li>The IEC has a permanent validity after registration</li>\r\n	<li>The IEC can be registered by the individuals and not just by the people who have registered themselves</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register for IEC?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The individuals do not have any compliance when it comes to the IEC</li>\r\n	<li>The person registered for the IEC is able to expand the business to the international market</li>\r\n	<li>Modifications in the IEC can be made if there are any modifications in the PAN card used for registration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Validity of IEC</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you register for the IEC, the lifetime validity is provided to the person. As PAN card is used for the registration, any form of modification in the same will lead to the modification in the IEC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Types of IEC</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The IEC is divided into two types depending upon the nature of the business. One if the merchant exporter and the other is the manufacturer exporter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Increase in opportunities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The purpose of IEC is to legalize import and export. Therefore, with this legal registration, the merchant or the manufacturer will be able to expand their business in the international circle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>PAN card of the director and the company</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of the cancelled cheque from the bank account</li>\r\n	<li>Passport size photograph</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Get the DSC and fill the application</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the documents and wait for the verification</li>\r\n	<li>Follow up with the officials and get the registration done</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:35:\"Import and Export Code registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:217:\"It is mandatory for a person to register for the import and export code in order to carry put import and export of goods within the country legally. A 10 digit code is provided to the person who registers for the IEC.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544353148_img3.jpg', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:29:08', '2018-12-10 18:17:10'),
(67, 1, 'Shop and establishment registration', 'shop-and-establishment-registration', '<p>People are required to register their shops and establishments if they plan on opening a shop, hotel or any commercial place within their state. It is required to get the license within 30 days of commencement of work.</p>', '<p><strong>What is shop and establishment?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People are required to register their shops and establishments if they plan on opening a shop, hotel or any commercial place within their state. Being a state based registration, it is required to get the license within 30 days of commencement of work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of the shop and establishment license?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>People who wish to start a commercial set-up in their state must compulsorily get the shops and establishment license</li>\r\n	<li>The shops and establishment license must be obtained within 30 days of the commencement of work</li>\r\n	<li>There are certain minimal compliances that must be followed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register for the shops and establishment?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>This registration helps to get uniform benefits for the employees in different sectors</li>\r\n	<li>It is easy to open a current bank account for the process</li>\r\n	<li>The license can be purchased as a proprietorship registration</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things that you should know</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The shop and establishment registration process has now been made fully electronic and every aspect of the process can be done online before and after the submission and verification of the required documents.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligible people</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Nearly all the shops and commercial spaces within the state are required to take up the shops and establishment license, if they wish to conduct their business within the state.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Objectives</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you register for the shops and establishment license, the employees are able to get some uniform benefits from the establishments and the state is also able to keep track of the commercial settings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sales deed or rental agreement for the proof of establishment</li>\r\n	<li>PAN card, ID proof and photograph of the person</li>\r\n	<li>Photographs of the exterior and the interior of the establishment</li>\r\n	<li>Details of the employees</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Submit the documents and get them validated</li>\r\n	<li>Fill out the application and submit them</li>\r\n	<li>Register for the license</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:35:\"Shop and establishment registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:218:\"People are required to register their shops and establishments if they plan on opening a shop, hotel or any commercial place within their state. It is required to get the license within 30 days of commencement of work.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544353257_img4.jpg', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:30:57', '2018-12-10 18:17:00'),
(68, 1, 'Trademark registration', 'trademark-registration', '<p>The trademark is the term given to something that defines the business done by a person. It can be logo or a pattern or any kind, which tells the other person about the business carried out by the company. Each company has a unique trademark name.</p>', '<p><strong>What is trademark?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trademark is the term given to something that defines the business done by a person. It can be logo or a pattern or any kind, which tells the other person about the business carried out by the company. Each company has a unique trademark name.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What are the features of trademark?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Trademark serves as the legal claim over the business</li>\r\n	<li>The trademark is considered to be the brand name of the company</li>\r\n	<li>The trademark serves as a protection for the business done by the company</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why should you register for the trademark?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The trademark creates a unique identity for the company</li>\r\n	<li>This creates a branding for the company which can be used in all places</li>\r\n	<li>The trademark is applicable nationwide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some things you should know about trademark</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Use of trademark</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once the trademark is registered, it can be used nationwide and the person using it illegally without permission can be sued. Once a national trademark is obtained, an international trademark can be got.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Business value</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The business value for the company increase once they get a trademark registered under their name. As it is considered to be a unique identity, no other company can make use of it in any way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Protection</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trademark provides complete protection for the business, along with serving as a protection for the branch in which the business is done. No other company can replicate or copy the trademark in any possible way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Documents required</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Requisition form for TM</li>\r\n	<li>Power of Attorney</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Process of registration</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Check for the availability of the trademark</li>\r\n	<li>Fill and submit the TM application form</li>\r\n	<li>Submit the documents for verification</li>\r\n	<li>TM is verified by the government</li>\r\n	<li>Registration can be done for the TM</li>\r\n</ul>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:22:\"Trademark registration\";s:11:\"description\";s:247:\"The trademark is the term given to something that defines the business done by a person. It can be logo or a pattern or any kind, which tells the other person about the business carried out by the company. Each company has a unique trademark name.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544353388_about-us-image.jpg', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:33:08', '2018-12-10 18:15:34'),
(69, 1, 'Comparison for Choosing for your Business formation ?', 'comparison-for-choosing-for-your-business-formation', '<p>Check below information to take decision about company formation.&nbsp;</p>', '<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Private Limited Company</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Public Limited Company</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Limited Liability Partnership Firm</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>One Person Company</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Partnership Firm</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Proprietorship Firm</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Recommendation for</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p>Startup Venture wants to distribute shares and Stock option having</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p>Wanted to go to Public for funding</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p>For Professional Services like Consultancy and Advocacy</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p>For Single owner want to have Private Limited Status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p>For Small Business Partners want to start in Unincorporated Form</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p>For Small Household business or For Single owner want to start in Unincorporated Form</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Integrity and Credibility </strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p>Having more integrity and Credibility because of already verified status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p>Having more integrity and Credibility because of already verified status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Having more integrity and Credibility because of already verified status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p>Having more integrity and Credibility because of already verified status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p>Having less integrity and credibility in comparison to Private Limited Status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Having less integrity and credibility in comparison to Private Limited Status</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Tax Rates and Tax Benefits</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p>Flat Tax @ 25% and Less Tax Benefits</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p>Flat Tax @ 25% and Less Tax Benefits</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Flat Tax @ 30% and Less More Tax benefit</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p>Flat Tax @ 25% and Less Tax Benefits</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p>Flat Tax @ 30% and Less Tax Benefits</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Tax Slab Rate&nbsp; from 5%-30% and more efficient in Tax.</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Limited Liability&nbsp; Benefit</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p>Yes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p>Yes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Yes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p>Yes</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p>No</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p>No</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<p><strong>Compliances</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p>High</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p>High</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Less</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p>High</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p>Minimal</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p>Minimal</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:62.35pt\">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.0pt\">\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://vsurecfo.com/service/private-limited-company-incorporation\">Start Now</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.8pt\">\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://vsurecfo.com/service/public-limited-company-registration\">Start Now</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:101.75pt\">\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://vsurecfo.com/service/llp-incorporation\">Start Now</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:102.15pt\">\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://vsurecfo.com/service/one-person-company-registration\">Start Now</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:97.55pt\">\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://vsurecfo.com/service/partnership-firm-registration\">Start Now</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:119.75pt\">\r\n			<p><a href=\"https://vsurecfo.com/service/proprietorship-firm\">Start Now</a></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>', 'a:2:{s:5:\"title\";s:53:\"Comparison Between Private Limited and Public Limited\";s:11:\"description\";s:65:\"Check below information to take decision about company formation.\";}', 'public/images/uploads/2018/Dec/1544353814_image.png', 'blog', NULL, NULL, 'publish', 'Template.SinglePost', 43, '2018-12-08 20:40:14', '2018-12-10 18:14:48'),
